import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['yield'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Barley'])
    plt.axhline(data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Yield: {data['yield'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    varieties = data['variety'].unique()
    locations = data['location'].unique()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    width = 0.1
    for i, variety in enumerate(varieties):
        variety_data = data[data['variety'] == variety]
        means = variety_data.groupby('location')['yield'].mean()
        ax.bar([x + i * width for x in range(len(locations))], means, width, label=variety)
    
    ax.set_xticks([x + width * (len(varieties) / 2 - 0.5) for x in range(len(locations))])
    ax.set_xticklabels(locations, rotation=45)
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_title('How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?')
    ax.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['nitrogen_level'], data['yield'])
    plt.xlabel('Nitrogen Level')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Yield vs Nitrogen Level'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['yield'], bins=10, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['yield'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(values='yield', index='variety', columns='site')
    ax = sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt=".2f")
    plt.title('How does the yield of different varieties of barley vary across sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Site')
    plt.ylabel('Variety')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
